'''Theodoor Gautier Thomas Pigeaud''' (20 February 1899 in [[Leipzig]] – 6 March 1988 in [[Gouda, South Holland|Gouda]]) was an expert in [[Java]]nese literature from the [[Netherlands]]. He especially became famous for his Java-Netherlands dictionary (1938) that Poerwadarminto chose as foundation of ''Baoesastra Djawa''. Moreover, Pigeaud was also known because of his monumental study about ''[[Nagarakretagama]]'' and text catalogues of the manuscripts in the libraries of [[Netherlands]], [[Denmark]], and [[Germany]].

